{
  "answer": "**The third couplet (sher) of chapter 33 in Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-E-Ghalib* reads:**\n\n> When beauty’s face, a sun at noon, inflames the gaze,  \n> And burns the sight itself, why hide in veils of haze?[^1]\n\nThis is from the English translation variant. In transliteration:  \n*jab woh jamaal-e-dilfaroz, soorat-e-mehr-e-neemroz,*  \n*aap hi ho nazaara-soz, parde mein munh chhupaaye kyun?*[^2]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 33, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/33-dil-hi-to-hai-na-sang-o-khisht-dard-se-bhar-na-aay/translation/#p-2775ab).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 33, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/33-dil-hi-to-hai-na-sang-o-khisht-dard-se-bhar-na-aay/transliteration/#p-2775ab).",
